What is the difference between a for loop and a while loop?
A while loop will repeat the function forever and ever for one assignment. A for loop will repeat only when certain specifications are met.

What are the four parts of a for loop? What do they do?
Starting the loop: what kind of loop, and why it loops.
Initialize variable: variable equals something.
Test for exit condition: how to exit the loop.
Incrementation: affecting the variable in what way.

What does "nested" mean in the context of nested loops?
Nested means loop within a loop.
